# Taste learning bench

## Verdict

No meaningful selection delta showed up: real history, nulled outcomes, and the synthetic negative flip all picked the same two memories at the same 4:1 split, with no holds and only wording/score noise.

## Method

- Repo: `/Users/joel/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer`
- Script: `.pi/extensions/observer/neat-memory-taste-bench.ts`
- Production state was read-only from `~/.joelclaw/observer-neat-memories.json`.
- Candidate sources matched production:
  - `/Users/joel/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard/.brain/observations`
  - `/Users/joel/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard/.brain/resources/retros`
- Prompt file matched production: `skills/neat-memory-simple-prompt.md`.
- Judge command matched production sandboxing: `pi -p --model openai-codex/gpt-5.6-sol:xhigh --no-tools --no-skills --no-context-files --no-extensions --no-session`.
- Prompt substitution matched `.pi/extensions/observer/neat-memory.ts`: `history` is the last 20 sent entries with `slug`, `sentAt`, `flavor`, and `outcome`; `candidates` are compact excerpts capped at 900 chars.
- Identical pool across arms: 120 unsent candidates from 356 current candidates.
- Repetitions: 5 per arm, 15 judge calls total.

## Arms

| Arm | History treatment | Graded entries visible |
| --- | --- | ---: |
| A | Real history as-is | 1 |
| B | Same history, every `outcome` set to null | 0 |
| C | Same history, every graded `outcome` set to `did-not-work` | 1 synthetic negative |

The one real graded entry was `2026-07-17-248a3715344a`, originally `worked`.

